{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-blog-post-jsx","path":"/silky-smooth-scrolling","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"html":"<p>If there was something that stood out the most to people when they have a go on a mac it’s how damn smooth the scrolling is, especially 2 finger scrolling using the trackpad. It didn’t take long for oems to realise they ought to add this functionality as Microsoft certainly wasn’t going to. But this turned out to be such an awfuly jerky, jumpy experience that most would deactivate the option, until now.</p>\n<p>Forum member MacHater over at <a href=\"http://forum.notebookreview.com/\">notebookreview</a> has released a stand alone program that greatly improves trackpad scrolling on windows pcs. It’s called TwoFingerScroll and allows heavy tweaking of the sensibility and whether to allow horizontal scrolling and even circular scrolling. You can also configure a variety of 2 and 3 finger gestures like 3 finger swipes for alt+tab providing a lion like window switcher.</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 361px; \"\n    >\n      <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 108.78378378378379%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"smooth scrolling\"\n        title=\"smooth scrolling\"\n        src=\"/static/8b939a80d05a027d9a9bd1d854dbc49d/39d76/twofingerscrollnew.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/8b939a80d05a027d9a9bd1d854dbc49d/12f09/twofingerscrollnew.png 148w,\n/static/8b939a80d05a027d9a9bd1d854dbc49d/e4a3f/twofingerscrollnew.png 295w,\n/static/8b939a80d05a027d9a9bd1d854dbc49d/39d76/twofingerscrollnew.png 361w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 361px) 100vw, 361px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n    </span></p>\n<p>I highly recommend this for any laptop user and you can grab it from the link below:</p>\n<p><a href=\"http://forum.notebookreview.com/hp-drivers-software-forum/552462-twofingerscroll-two-finger-scrolling-done-right-more.html\">DOWNLOAD</a></p>","frontmatter":{"date":"May 19, 2012","path":"/silky-smooth-scrolling","tags":["tag"],"title":"Silky Smooth Scrolling","image":{"childImageSharp":{"resize":{"src":"/static/4e9a95cf7025f7dc1da351e45e9f97b3/458e6/balloons.jpg"}}}}}},"pageContext":{"prev":{"excerpt":"Put aside finals for an hour to get started on #gsoc, implemented only one function but the rest that I have set in this period shouldn’t take long to add. 80% of the time was reminding myself how it all works and another 10% from the lag of the…","html":"<p>Put aside finals for an hour to get started on #gsoc, implemented only one function but the rest that I have set in this period shouldn’t take long to add. 80% of the time was reminding myself how it all works and another 10% from the lag of the android vm.</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 580px; \"\n    >\n      <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 56.08108108108109%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"pandora\"\n        title=\"pandora\"\n        src=\"/static/8855d65a7e2726f7f18641a1d31cc7e3/b6272/pandora-1024x575.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/8855d65a7e2726f7f18641a1d31cc7e3/12f09/pandora-1024x575.png 148w,\n/static/8855d65a7e2726f7f18641a1d31cc7e3/e4a3f/pandora-1024x575.png 295w,\n/static/8855d65a7e2726f7f18641a1d31cc7e3/b6272/pandora-1024x575.p